<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910924-0144</DOCNO><DOCID>910924-0144.</DOCID><HL>   Technology:   Lotus Mail-Forwarding Software</HL><DATE>09/24/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   AAPL IBM LOTS</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>COMPUTERS AND INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (CPR)SOFTWARE (SOF)</IN><NS>NEW PRODUCTS andamp; SERVICES (PDT)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)MASSACHUSETTS (MA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   CAMBRIDGE, Mass. -- Lotus Development Corp. introducedmail-forwarding software that was quickly embraced byInternational Business Machines Corp. and Apple Computer Inc.and could become an industry standard.   The product, Open Messaging Interface, enables users tosend messages without exiting the program on which they'reworking.</LP><TEXT>   Apple and IBM will include the technology in some of theirfuture computers, the software developer said.   Lotus said OMI will be available in 60 days to developersfor inclusion into their products.</TEXT></DOC>